did.physloc: Special Collections and University Archives materials are stored offsite and must be paged 36-48 hours in advance. For more information on paging collections, see the department's website: http://library.stanford.edu/depts/spc/spc.html.
did.abstract: Meeting minutes, photographs and posters documenting the Department of Art and Art History.

accessrestrict.head: Access to Collection
accessrestrict.p: Emeriti files in Series 3 & Accession ARCH-2017-010 are Restricted for 75 years from date of creation. Otherwise, the materials are open for research use. Audio-visual materials are not available in original format, and must be reformatted to a digital use copy.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: All requests to reproduce, publish, quote from, or otherwise use collection materials must be submitted in writing to the Head of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, California 94305-6064. Consent is given on behalf of Special Collections as the owner of the physical items and is not intended to include or imply permission from the copyright owner. Such permission must be obtained from the copyright owner, heir(s) or assigns. See: http://library.stanford.edu/depts/spc/pubserv/permissions.html.
Restrictions also apply to digital representations of the original materials. Use of digital files is restricted to research and educational purposes.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [identification of item], Stanford University, Department of Art and Art History, Records (SC1101). Dept. of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of departmental meeting minutes, photographs and posters documenting the Department of Art and Art History.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged in four series: Series 1. Administrative Records; Series 2. Photographs; Series 3. Emeriti files; Series 4. Posters.
